  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" Umashankar Yadav & Anr. versus State of Uttar Pradesh, Through Chief Secretary & Anr. pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_5_1306_1315','2025INSC653'); ><font size='4'> <strong>UMASHANKAR YADAV & ANR.<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>STATE OF UTTAR PRADESH, THROUGH CHIEF SECRETARY & ANR. </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 5 S.C.R. 1306</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 653</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006032025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : PAMIDIGHANTAM SRI NARASIMHA<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, JOYMALYA BAGCHI</strong><br> Issue for Consideration Whether the High Court erred by not quashing the prosecution against the accused under ss.186 and 353 of Indian Penal Code. Headnotes&dagger; Penal Code, 1860 &ndash; s.186 &ndash; Whether the Chargesheet discloses the ingredients of offence was conducted by the labour officers on the tip of social workers(appellants) to verify the allegation that bonded/child labour were employed at the brick kiln, the appellant accompanied the labour officers for the raid &ndash; During inspection, a difference of opinion cropped up between the<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 08-05-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CRIMINAL APPEAL No. 439/2018</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_5_1306_1315','2025INSC653','S')><i <i class='fas